The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden during the July Fourth celebration at the White House. They express gratitude for the performers and military families in attendance and emphasize the power of music to uplift and unite. President Biden jokes about renting the White House and thanks the audience for their support. He also highlights the importance of showing support for the military and reaffirms America's role as a leading nation. The President concludes by introducing the next performer, Ne-Yo, and urging everyone to enjoy the rest of the evening.